  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EEveryone loves payday! Here\u0027s what you need to know about how and when you\u2019ll be paid:\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPay Schedule:\u003C/strong\u003E We pay employees on a bi-weekly basis. If a payday falls on a holiday or weekend, you\u2019ll receive your paycheck on the preceding business day.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPay Cycle:\u003C/strong\u003E Our standard payroll cycle runs from \u003Cem\u003EMonday through Sunday\u003C/em\u003E and pays out every other Friday.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHourly Employees:\u003C/strong\u003E Pay is issued one pay period in arrears. For example, hours worked from the 1st through the 15th will be paid on the last day of the month.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommission Payments:\u003C/strong\u003E To receive commission, you must be actively employed on the date the commission is paid through payroll. Commissions and bonuses are not considered earned until they are actually paid.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EIf you have any questions about your paycheck or payment schedule, please contact \u003Cstrong\u003EPayroll\u003C/strong\u003E or your \u003Cstrong\u003EHR Business Partner\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
