    <summary>
      <Value><![CDATA[Everyone loves payday! Paydays are bi-weekly. If a payday falls on a holiday or weekend, you’ll be paid on the preceding workday. 

Our pay cycle runs Monday through Sunday, to be paid every other Friday.

Hourly employees are paid one pay period in arrears. For example, hourly employees are paid on the last day of the month for hours worked during the 1st through the 15th. 

Employees eligible for commission must be actively employed on the date commission is paid through payroll. Commissions and bonuses are not considered earned until actually paid to the employee.]]></Value>
